        "LIGHT-LEGGED": "Nimble; swift of foot. Sir P. Sidney.",
        "LIGHT-MINDED": "Unsettled; unsteady; volatile; not considerate.-- Light\"-mind`ed*ness, n.",
        "LIGHT-SHIP": "A vessel carrying at the masthead a brilliant light, and mooredoff a shoal or place of dangerous navigation as a guide for mariners.",
