        "LIGHTSTRUCK": "Damaged by accidental exposure to light; light-fogged; -- saidof plates or films.",
        "LIGHTWEIGHT": "Light in weight, as a coin; specif., applied to a man or animalwho is a lightweight.",
        "LIGHTWOOD": "Pine wood abounding in pitch, used for torches in the SouthernUnited States; pine knots, dry sticks, and the like, for kindling afire quickly or making a blaze.",
        "LIGHTY": "Illuminated. [Obs.] Wyclif.",
        "LIGNEOUS": "Made of wood; consisting of wood; of the nature of, orresembling, wood; woody.It should be tried with shoots of vines and roots of red roses; forit may be they, being of a moreligneous nature, will incorporate withthe tree itself. Bacon.Ligneous marble, wood coated or prepared so as to resemble marble.",
        "LIGNIFEROUS": "Yielding or producing wood.",
        "LIGNIFICATION": "A change in the character of a cell wall, by which it becomesharder. It is supposed to be due to an incrustation of lignin.",
