        "LIQUID AIR": "A transparent limpid liquid, slightly blue in color, consistingof a mixture of liquefied oxygen and nitrogen. It is prepared bysubjecting air to great pressure and then cooling it by its ownexpansion to a temperature below the boiling point of itsconstituents  (N -194º C; O -183º C.).",
