        "LOGWOOD": "The heartwood of a tree (Hæmatoxylon Campechianum), a native ofSouth America, It is a red, heavy wood, containing a crystallinesubstance called hæmatoxylin, and is used largely in dyeing. Anextract from this wood is used in medicine as an astringent. Alsocalled Campeachy wood, and bloodwood.",
